# No agent gcloud secrets or env-var proposals

This is the authoritative R&D contract. Every other R&D `rules/*.mdc` file and mission `SKILL.md` cites or restates it.

| Action | Binding rule |
|--------|--------------|
| Updating gcloud secrets or equivalent cloud secret stores | **Forbidden for agents.** |
| Adding or wiring environment variables in application or infrastructure code (`.env`, config maps, secret references, CI environment, Terraform/Pulumi secret variables, and similar mechanisms) | **Forbidden** unless the developer gives an **explicit same-turn instruction** naming the variable. |
| Proposing new environment variables in plans, PR notes, follow-ups, structured-choice options, or chat | **Forbidden.** Never suggest environment variables as a solution. |
| Explicit same-turn developer instruction for a named environment variable | **Allowed only for that variable.** Do not invent others. |

## Default when blocked

Prefer existing configuration, existing repository feature flags, or documented hosting rules. Otherwise, ask how configuration should be supplied without offering environment-variable options.

## Related

Hosting overlays may add repository-specific secret tooling but cannot weaken this ban.
